  "title" : "Eclipse is only allowing maven not java",
  "body" : "<p>I am running into what I hope is a very simple problem. I have downloaded eclipse, installed it, opened an existing project. The project had some errors and I ended up removing the project from the file explorer on the left. I wanted to start fresh. Now it is only letting me create new Maven projects. When I try to use any of the icons for new projects or files, or if I go to the top and select file--&gt; new it is only allowing Maven. I would only like to create java projects. I have never run into this problem before and I do not know what I have done to cause this problem or how to get out of it.\nHow do I get back to just making java projects?</p>\n<p>This is what the screen looks like\n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/V0j8spwt.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/V0j8spwt.png\" alt=\"Eclipse Editor\" /></a></p>\n"
